Besides band gap, carrier effective mass and carrier concentration are other key parameters for the semiconductor transport performance. The magnitude of the Seebeck coefficient is directly related to the dispersion of energy levels near the Fermi level. The relation of the Seebeck coefficient with carrier concentration and effective mass is: S=8π2kB23eℏ2m∗Tπ3n2/3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
